{
  "texts": [
    "They need to construct a tree structure for each example, which is labor-intensive.",
    "Neither of these two methods captured the interaction between event types and trigger words, resulting in suboptimal event detection performance.",
    "Hsu et al. [19] proposed a generation-based method called DEGREE and manually designed a prompt containing event type descriptions and event keywords.",
    "DEGREE got excellent performance on event extraction, especially under lowresource conditions.",
    "But the design process of its prompt costs a lot of manual work, which is unacceptable in real-world applications."
  ]
}